commit_list.message:
Fix bug where the wrong author info is used for committing

The author information is saved in the buffer-local variable 'process-environment' in
the log-edit buffer.
To reset its value, kill-local-variable must be called not after, but BEFORE
switching away from the log-edit buffer.

Otherwise, the old author information will be reapplied in the next commit that uses
the same log-edit buffer.

commit_list.message:
home-manager: exit with an error on build failure

Because 'set -e' has no effect on commands that run in an if condition,
the script was always exiting with no error when 'doBuild' failed.

As a bonus, $wrkdir is now always removed after building.

commit_list.message:
home-environment: fix error when deleting empty directories

With --ignore-fail-on-non-empty, non-emptiness is the only failure
that gets ignored by rmdir. In the case that rmdir reaches $HOME and
considers deleting it, it will detect insufficient permissions and
subsequently exit with an error, even if $HOME is not empty.

Prevent this by calling rmdir with a relative path that excludes
$HOME.

their names without providing a target or source attribute.

[Rename] handleEvent -> handleKeyEvent. handleEvent is reserved on newer OS X versions
Window#child_window: Get child window by class name

Fix release_core_modifiers by releasing the exact keys that were pressed.

Distinct physical keys that are functionally equivalent (such as left/right shift)
are treated as the same key by Rum's default layouts. (See Layout#remap)
Previously, release_core_modifiers sent key-up events for the same generic physical
key, regardless of which side specific key had been pressed before.

These inaccurate up-events (e.g. left shift when right shift had been pressed) aren't
recognized by some applications such as Chrome—they act as if the modifier were
still pressed.

This is fixed by keeping track of the exact ids of pressed modifiers.

[Fix] Emacs-Interaction: Return nil instead of '' when Emacs is not running.

That's what its clients are expecting.

Fix Git errors being inserted into user buffers

Introduce 'git-gutter+-insert-git-output' for calls to Git that use Git's
standard output. For now, any output to stderr is ignored.

'git-gutter+-call-git' now ignores any output from Git.
Also, it returns t on zero exit code instead of the exit code itself.
Silence byte-compiler warning in compiled defadvice
unstage-whole-buffer: Unstage only the current buffer

Handle git diff errors

This fixes a runtime error that was raised when 'git-gutter+-diff' returned
nil after 'git diff' failed.
Fix the splitting logic for displaying the staged changes buffer
Readme: Add animated GIF to show staging/committing
Refresh when a buffer is staged or unstaged in Magit
Add a comment about newer Magit versions

Fix commit message history cycling

By locally resetting 'log-edit-comment-ring-index',
'M-p' is now guaranteed to insert the previous commit message

Support the latest 'git-commit-mode'

Don't derive from 'git-commit-mode', but copy the initial setup code and
omit statements concerning async committing.

This fixes a bug where output from a diff subprocess was inserted into the commit
message buffer because `kill-buffer-query-functions' was modified by 'git-commit-mode'.

Add 'stage-and-commit-whole-buffer', 'unstage-whole-buffer'

Trivial, but superbly helpful in day-to-day git use.
Add changes in master branch to changelog

Don't use 'mark-whole-buffer' for 'stage-whole-buffer'

'mark-whole-buffer' has the unwanted side effect of changing the user's
mark ring.

Drop Marmalade support.

Version 0.14 of `git-commit-mode', which git-gutter+ depends on, isn't
available on Marmalade.

Support the latest git-commit-mode

Many thanks to Akinori MUSHA for providing a first draft.

Don't define commit-mode-map as a constant

Mode maps are open for modification. It's weird to mark them as
constant.

define-derived-mode internally defines 'git-gutter+-commit-mode-map'.
So use setq instead of defvar.
Add custom commit interface based on git-commit-mode
Allow reverting hunks within the region

Rename and improve 'call-on-current-buffer'

This unifies the interfaces of 'call-git' and 'call-on-current-buffer'

Add 'git-gutter+-enable-default-display-mode'

This helps toggling between the default and the fringe display mode.
Readme: Convert to Markdown underlined header syntax

Remove unneeded autoloads

Calling these commands only makes sense when 'git-gutter+-mode' is
active. In this case, 'git-gutter+.el' has already been loaded.

Don't lose the window config when restarting a commit

'git-gutter+-commit' can now be called twice in a row without losing
the original window config.

Only call 'root-directory' for remote files

This saves us an extra call to Git for regular, local files and makes
'git-gutter+-refresh' a bit snappier.

Use relative paths when calling Git on Windows

On Unix, use absolute paths:
When a file has been opened via a symlink, 'file-relative-name' will
fail because 'git-gutter:root-directory' (which points to the original
directory) and 'buffer-file-name' (which holds the link alias) don't
match up.

(On Windows, 'buffer-file-name' always returns the original file
name, so 'file-relative-name' is safe to use.)

Fixes #1

Fix diff buffer erasing

When 'diff-default-read-only' is t, diff buffers must be made
writeable before changing their contents.

(Reported by Jinseop Kim)

Use 'call-process' instead of 'call-process-shell-command'

This obviates shell quoting any file names.
And it's slighty faster.

Remove deprecated mode-on/off-hooks.

These hooks are undocumented and deprecated.

Remove git-gutter:toggle

Calling 'git-gutter-mode' works just fine for toggling
Only warn about nonexisting Git repo when interactively called

Simplify 'check-file-and-directory'.

There's no need to check for global-git-gutter-mode
Skip trailing newline when extracting the last diff hunk

Fix diffinfo line numbers for deleted hunks

Increase them by one. Now they show up in the right position and deleted
hunks at line 1 won't be ignored by 'search-here-diffinfo'.
Avoid redundant diff calculations when reverting
Optimized global mode that avoids redundant diff calculations on file loading

Reset window margins on `window-configuration-change-hook'

git-gutter-fringe can ignore the hook by setting
`window-config-change-function' to nil.

Don't use idle-timer to run `git-gutter'

When called by idle-timer, `git-gutter' will run in the currently active
buffer, instead of the buffer from which `run-with-idle-timer' was called.
This causes a bug when  `global-git-gutter-mode' turns on `git-gutter-mode'
in a currently inactive buffer.

Revert 'introduce minimal update interval(Default is 1 second)',
revert 'Add explanation of updating gutter threshold'

Revert 'Remove unneeded function call',
revert 'Users can control update gutter hook points'

Remove init function

It's not needed anymore for git-gutter-fringe

Add `clear-diff-infos' as the default clear-function

Remove default call to `remove-overlays' which is not needed for git-gutter-fringe

Remove redundant call to `git-gutter'

It's automatically run by the `after-save-hook'

Revert "Use full path for 'git diff'"

Using full paths breaks git-gutter on 'MinGW Emacs + Cygwin Git' platforms
because Cygwin Git can't handle absolute Windows file paths.
Make ido-imenu recognize the symbol at point.
Make ido-imenu recognize the symbol at point.
Make ido-imenu recognize the symbol at point.
